# UI Image Safety — Automari Website

## Hard stops (never do these)

- Do NOT change `Navigation.tsx`, `app/page.tsx`, `app/layout.tsx`, or `HeroSection.tsx` unless the user explicitly asks to edit that exact file in the current message.
- Do NOT replace a compact logo lockup (icon + text) with a full-width or full-bleed brand image.
- Do NOT use `next/image` with `fill` unless the parent has **both** `position: relative` **and** explicit pixel bounds (`w-*` + `h-*`, never unbounded).
- Do NOT add new images to the homepage/nav without explicit `width`, `height`, and `max-w-*` / `max-h-*` classes.
- Do NOT run `rm -rf .next`, kill dev servers, or restart production unless the user asks or a build is required after a verified fix.

## Scope for chatbot / logo requests

When the user asks for chatbot or logo changes:

1. **Only edit** files under `components/Chatbot/`, `components/chat/`, and `lib/ai/`.
2. Nav logo changes require explicit user approval in the same message.
3. Prefer `/automari-icon-transparent.png` for chatbot slots (FAB, avatars, chat header). Do not use large wordmark images in small UI slots.

## Required image pattern

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD — explicit dimensions, bounded
<Image
  src="/automari-icon-transparent.png"
  alt="Automari.Ai"
  width={32}
  height={32}
  className="h-8 w-8 max-h-8 max-w-8 object-contain"
/>

// ❌ BAD — fill in a loose or unbounded container
<div className="flex items-center">
  <Image src="/automari-icon-transparent.png" fill className="object-contain" />
</div>
```

## Size limits

| Location | Max size |
|----------|----------|
| Nav wordmark | `max-h-7`, `max-w-[120px]` |
| Chat header logo | `max-h-8`, `max-w-8` |
| Floating chat button | `w-14 h-14` button, logo `max-h-9 max-w-9` inside |
| Hero / marketing | Do not touch without explicit request |

## Before finishing any UI change

1. Confirm only chatbot-scoped files changed (or user-approved files).
2. Run `npm run build` — must pass.
3. Verify homepage returns 200 and nav is still compact (icon ~44px + text, not a large banner).
